This paper deals with the problem of multiclass prediction using few shared features, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper discusses an algorithm called ShareBoost, which is designed to efficiently find a predictor that uses few shared features and has a small generalization error. This problem is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Given the focus of the paper on machine learning and the use of natural data sets in experiments, it is most likely to belong to the cs.LG sub-category, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.DS.
